By Ebere Agozie The Federal Government and U.S. Government say positive messaging and consensus building among Executive, Legislature and Judiciary are key to addressing security challenges in the country. Both countries made the disclosure during the bilateral discussion between the U.S. Ambassador to Nigeria; Mary Leonard, and the Attorney-General of the Federation and Minister of Justice Abubakar Malami, SAN. The two countries during  the meeting agreed on  the need for effective partnership in ensuring safe, secured and prosperous Nigeria.  Both countries also affirmed that laws are meant to achieve collective peace among the people. They equally agreed that governance is about improving the welfare of the majority of the people, maintaining that holistic approach is needed in striking the balance between public interest and rights of individual citizens. Malami expressed satisfaction with the support and mutual understanding between Nigeria and the U.S. in the fight against corruption, repatriation of looted funds and extradition of people involved in terrorism financing. Responding, Leonard expressed willingness and determination of the US to support Nigeria in the fight against insecurity. (NAN) Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Like this:Like Loading... Like Loading...  	Related FG to resuscitate special terrorism prosecution courts, says MalamiBy Ebere Agozie The Federal Government will soon resuscitate Special Terrorism Prosecution Courts, the Minister of Justice, Abubakar Malami has said. Malami made this known in a statement by Dr Umar Gwandu his Special Assistant on Media and Public Relations on Thursday in Abuja. The move, Malami said is geared towards…May 13,